data.name: Chickpea and Herb Patties with Tahini Sauce
data.quickTastyDescription: Savory chickpea patties infused with fresh herbs served with a creamy tahini sauce.
detailedCookingInstructions: Drain and rinse the chickpeas, then mash them in a bowl until mostly smooth.
Stir in the chopped herbs, garlic, green onion, cumin, coriander, salt, and pepper.
Add the egg and breadcrumbs, mixing until combined. Form into patties.
Heat olive oil in a skillet over medium heat and fry the patties for about 5 minutes on each side or until golden brown.
For the tahini sauce, whisk together tahini, lemon juice, and enough water to achieve a smooth consistency. Season with salt to taste.
Serve the patties warm drizzled with tahini sauce.
